<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:local="clr-namespace:mahjongNEA"
              ColumnWidth="400" FontSize="14" FontFamily="Georgia">
    <Paragraph FontSize="18">
        <Bold FontSize="22">
            Complete Hand:
        </Bold>
        <LineBreak/>
        A complete hand contains 4 melds and an eye.
        <LineBreak/>
        <LineBreak/>
        A meld can be one of the following:
        <LineBreak/>
        <Bold FontSize="18">Kong:</Bold> 3 of the same tile.
        <LineBreak/>
        <Bold FontSize="18">Pong:</Bold> 4 of the same tile.
        <LineBreak/>
        <Bold FontSize="18">Chow:</Bold> 3 consecutive tiles of the same suit.
        <LineBreak/>
        <LineBreak/>
        <Bold FontSize="18">Eye:</Bold> a pair of the same time.
        <LineBreak/>
        <LineBreak/>
        Melds formed counts towards the 4 needed whether it is walled or not.
        <LineBreak/>
        However, tiles in walled melds cannot be changed anymore while tiles in unwalled melds can be changed.
        <LineBreak/>
        <LineBreak/>
        This hand has a base faan value of 0.
        <LineBreak/>
        Higher faan value hands are formed by satisfying certain conditions with the 4 melds and eye.
        <LineBreak/>
        If a hand satisfies the conditions of multiple different hands, the faan value is additive unless specified.
        <LineBreak/>
        Some special hands doesn't consist of 4 melds and an eye but instead requires specific conditions to be met.
        <LineBreak/>
        For all faan values of hands, see the menu in the drop down by clicking on the "Winning Hands" section.
    </Paragraph>
</FlowDocument>
